<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chun &amp; Tsiang., J. Arnold Arbor. 28: 324" authorityYear="1947" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus disciformis" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="disciformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Quercus disciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed from Guizhou to Guangdong and Hainan in China and not recorded as a threatened species in 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org" refId="B17" refString="IUCN, 2017. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2017-2. http://www.iucnredlist.org" title="The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2017 - 2." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. The Vietnamese population in Ba Vi National Park extends its distribution range, representing the south western limit. Given the situation, the population in Vietnam is locally important but the category Least Concern (LC) (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" publicationUrl="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/redlist_cats_crit_en.pdf" refId="B16" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK. http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/redlist_cats_crit_en.pdf" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." url="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/redlist_cats_crit_en.pdf" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban, NT" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="B3" refString="Ban, NT, Ly, DT, Tap, N, Dung, VV, Thin, NN, Tien, VN, Khoi, KN, 2007. Vietnam Red Data Book Part II. Plants. Natural Sciences and Technology Publishers, Hanoi. [In Vietnamese]" title="Vietnam Red Data Book Part II. Plants. Natural Sciences and Technology Publishers, Hanoi. [In Vietnamese]" year="2007">Ban et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) would be appropriate for this species.
</paragraph>
